article.description: — Jalen Williams had 24 points and five assists as Santa Clara raced past Portland 91-67 in the quarterfinals of the West Coast Conference tournament on Saturday night.
article.headline: Williams helps Santa Clara oust Portland in WCC tourney
article.linkText: Williams helps Santa Clara oust Portland in WCC tourney
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — Jalen Williams had 24 points and five assists as Santa Clara raced past Portland 91-67 in the quarterfinals of the West Coast Conference tournament on Saturday night. PJ Pipes pitched in with 21 points, five rebounds and five assists for the Broncos (21-10). Josip Vrankic added 19 points, seven rebounds and five assists. Keshawn Justice scored 16 with seven boards. Chris Austin topped the Pilots (18-14) with 19 points. Tyler Robertson had 14 points and six rebounds. Third-seeded Santa Clara advances to place No. 2 seed Saint Mary's on Monday night. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25
